<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// isRenamable - Returns true if this register may be renamed, i.e. it does</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// not generate a value that is somehow read in a way that is not represented</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// by the Machine IR (e.g. to meet an ABI or ISA requirement).  This is only</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// valid on physical register operands.  Virtual registers are assumed to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// always be renamable regardless of the value of this field.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="414"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Operands that are renamable can freely be changed to any other register</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// that is a member of the register class returned by</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// MI-&gt;getRegClassConstraint().</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// isRenamable can return false for several different reasons:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - ABI constraints (since liveness is not always precisely modeled).  We</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="422"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   conservatively handle these cases by setting all physical register</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00423" /><CodeLine lineNumber="423"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   operands that didn’t start out as virtual regs to not be renamable.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00424" /><CodeLine lineNumber="424"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   Also any physical register operands created after register allocation or</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="425"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   whose register is changed after register allocation will not be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="426"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   renamable.  This state is tracked in the MachineOperand::IsRenamable</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="427"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   bit.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00428" /><CodeLine lineNumber="428"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00429" /><CodeLine lineNumber="429"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - Opcode/target constraints: for opcodes that have complex register class</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="430"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   requirements (e.g. that depend on other operands/instructions), we set</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00431" /><CodeLine lineNumber="431"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   hasExtraSrcRegAllocReq/hasExtraDstRegAllocReq in the machine opcode</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00432" /><CodeLine lineNumber="432"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   description.  Operands belonging to instructions with opcodes that are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00433" /><CodeLine lineNumber="433"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   marked hasExtraSrcRegAllocReq/hasExtraDstRegAllocReq return false from</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00434" /><CodeLine lineNumber="434"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   isRenamable().  Additionally, the AllowRegisterRenaming target property</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00435" /><CodeLine lineNumber="435"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   prevents any operands from being marked renamable for targets that don&#39;t</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00436" /><CodeLine lineNumber="436"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   have detailed opcode hasExtraSrcRegAllocReq/hasExtraDstRegAllocReq</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00437" /><CodeLine lineNumber="437"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   values.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="438"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineoperand/#a8be49bc86b5d01b52b90baf1b4477667">isRenamable</a>() </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00921" /><CodeLine lineNumber="921"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// CreateRegMask - Creates a register mask operand referencing Mask.  The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00922" /><CodeLine lineNumber="922"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// operand does not take ownership of the memory referenced by Mask, it</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00923" /><CodeLine lineNumber="923"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// must remain valid for the lifetime of the operand.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00924" /><CodeLine lineNumber="924"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00925" /><CodeLine lineNumber="925"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// A RegMask operand represents a set of non-clobbered physical registers</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00926" /><CodeLine lineNumber="926"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// on an instruction that clobbers many registers, typically a call.  The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00927" /><CodeLine lineNumber="927"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// bit mask has a bit set for each physreg that is preserved by this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00928" /><CodeLine lineNumber="928"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// instruction, as described in the documentation for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00929" /><CodeLine lineNumber="929"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// TargetRegisterInfo::getCallPreservedMask().</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00930" /><CodeLine lineNumber="930"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00931" /><CodeLine lineNumber="931"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Any physreg with a 0 bit in the mask is clobbered by the instruction.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00932" /><CodeLine lineNumber="932"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00933" /><CodeLine lineNumber="933" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineoperand/#a4c01d756ca363aef75429d61d21c0c14"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> MachineOperand <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineoperand/#a4c01d756ca363aef75429d61d21c0c14">CreateRegMask</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint32&#95;t &#42;Mask) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
